Amoskeag Bank Shares Inc and&lt;Portsmouth Savings Bank> said they will file motions for arehearing with the New Hampshire Supreme Court of its March 30ruling that overturned state regulatory approval of Amoskeag'sacquisition Portsmouth.    "The ramifications of this decision, we believe, go wellbeyond the affiliation of Amoskeag and Portsmouth SavingsBank," said Amoskeag chairman William S. Bushnell.    The transaction was opposed by a group of Portsmouthinvestors who wanted the bank to remain independent, accordingto press reports. Reuter&#3;